==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛltə(r)|-ɛltə(r)]]

===Noun===
'''shelter'''
#A [[refuge]], [[haven]] or other [[cover]] or [[protection]] from something
#An [[institution]] that [[provide]]s [[temporary]] [[housing]] for [[homeless]] [[people]], [[battered]] [[women]] etc

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[suojapaikka]] (1), [[turvapaikka]] (1)
*German: [[Zuflucht]] ''f'' (1), [[Obdach]] ''n'' (1), [[Zufluchtsort]] {{m}}
*Italian: [[rifugio]]

===Verb===
'''to shelter''' [[transitive]] or [[intransitive]]
#To [[provide]] or [[take]] cover

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[suojautua]] (''to take cover''), [[suojata]] (''to provide cover'')
*French: [[abri]] (''a shelter''), [[abriter]] (''to provide cover'')

